@BeleuchteteBrueder Of course, Chrono Cross is way more complex and ambitious than Chrono Trigger (which remain a good but childish game), in every field: gameplay, background and of course story, I've never seen a scenario more deep and complex since Xenogears. The problem in CC, is that it isn't as "well-made" as CT, it's difficult to explain well in English where mon vocabulary lacks: CT is easy to get into, isn't boring at any moment, and the storytelling is just perfect, with the right surprises at the right moment.
Somewhat, CC is more hardcore gamers than CT, but I like both as much as the other, just in a completely different way. Those two games are almost opposite from each other, your preference can only depend on your taste.

As for Zelda ok maybe I misunderstood.

