snippet.textDisplay:
@BeleuchteteBrueder Woah. I disagree with almost everything you said about the gameplay. Except that the boss battle were substantially easier, of course. Because that's true. ^_^'

I found sailing the open waters to be a joy (the enjoyment lasted longer than Assassin's Creed Black Flag, so that's something) finding islands with all kinds of things to find, meeting all kinds of silly characters in true Zelda-esque fashion. The dungeons were all fun to traverse though (except for the F**KING WATER TEMPLE ASDFGHGF) , etc etc. It definitely didn't feel empty to me. Maybe it's because I like sailing so much. Mhm. Anyway, combine all that with the lovely music and unique artstyle, and this is easily my pick for the best Zelda. (yes, I did play Majora's Mask, Twilight Princess, and finished Ocarina of Time)

I guess experiences just differ with each person? Looking at your thoughts and opinions about Wind Waker, it's almost as if we both played a different game, lol ^_^'

